    1 # Privacy Policy for Classic Offline Games Room
    2
    3 **Effective Date: February 19, 2026**
    4
    5 Classic Offline Games Room ("we," "our," or "us") is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and
      disclose information when you use our mobile application.
    6
    7 ## 1. Information We Collect
    8
    9 ### 1.1 Information Collected Automatically
   10 When you use the app, we may collect certain information automatically, including:
   11 *   **Usage Data:** Information about how you interact with the app, such as games played, high scores, and time spent in the app.
   12 *   **Device Information:** We may collect information about your mobile device, such as device model, operating system version, and unique device
      identifiers.
   13
   14 ### 1.2 Third-Party Services
   15 We use third-party services that may collect information used to identify you:
   16 *   **Google Play Services:** Used for app functionality and updates.
   17 *   **Google AdMob:** We use Google AdMob to display advertisements. AdMob may collect and use data (such as advertising IDs) to show personalized or
      non-personalized ads.
   18 *   **Firebase Analytics:** We use Firebase to understand app usage and improve the user experience.
   19
   20 ## 2. How We Use Your Information
   21 We use the information we collect to:
   22 *   Provide and maintain the app's functionality.
   23 *   Improve and personalize your experience.
   24 *   Monitor and analyze usage and trends.
   25 *   Show relevant advertisements.
   26
   27 ## 3. Data Storage and Offline Support
   28 Most of your game data (high scores, settings) is stored locally on your device using `AsyncStorage`. This data remains on your device unless you clea
      the app's cache or uninstall it.
   29
   30 ## 4. Children's Privacy
   31 Our app is intended for a general audience. We do not knowingly collect personally identifiable information from children under 13.
   32
   33 ## 5. Your Choices
   34 You can manage your ad preferences through your device settings (e.g., "Limit Ad Tracking" on iOS or "Opt out of Interest-Based Ads" on Android).
   35
   36 ## 6. Changes to This Privacy Policy
   37 We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page.
   38
   39 ## 7. Contact Us
   40 If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at: colindiffer@gmail.com
